# 1C Coding Standards — Loader

The canonical standards live in docs, not in this rule file.

When writing or reviewing BSL, read the relevant references:

1. `.cursor/docs/1c-coding-standards.md`
2. `.cursor/docs/standard/1c-standards-navigator.md`
3. The domain file from `.cursor/docs/standard/std-*.md` that matches the touched code
4. For review only: `.cursor/rules/bsl-antipatterns.mdc` and `.cursor/docs/antipatterns/bsl-antipatterns.md`

Do not duplicate long standards in runtime rules. Keep this file as a glob-triggered redirect only.
